**NOTE** : Please do try **UNIQUE PATH** problem before trying this problem : https://leetcode.com/problems/unique-paths/
and my solution and explanation to that problem is : https://leetcode.com/problems/unique-paths/discuss/2364894/JAVA-SOLUTION-or-0MS-100-FASTER-or-FULL-EXPLANATION

Now coming to this problem :
* we can move either down or right 
* for the grid[0][0] we don't update it.
* so for the 0th row or column we will update the cost by adding the cost before that column i.e
1.  			for the 0th row --> grid[i][j] += grid[i][j-1]
1.  			for the 0th col --> grid[i][j] += grid[i-1][j];



* Now for the other elements we update them adding that block value to **MIN** of the value from top element above them and the left element to that block (since we can from either down or right , therefor to reach any element we enter in it either from top of it of left of it )

```
public int minPathSum(int[][] grid) {
        int m = grid.length;
        int n= grid[0].length;
        for(int i=0;i<m;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                if(i==0 && j==0) continue;
                else if (i == 0){
                    grid[i][j] += grid[i][j-1];
                }
                else if(j == 0){
                    grid[i][j] += grid[i-1][j];
                }
                else {
                    grid[i][j] += Math.min(grid[i-1][j],grid[i][j-1]);
                }
            }
        }
        return grid[m-1][n-1];
    }
