<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Just the brute force way.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. --> 
Simply we create a **max variable** and intilize it with zero and **check the difference** of the elements and **update max if greater** than the earlier value stored in it.

![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/1f3ad12b-6c3e-4f51-b127-a2c50cfacf57_1681293191.8231432.png)



# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(nlogn)-> **As we are using only one loop and sort inbuilt function.**
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


- Space complexity:O(1)-> **No extra space created**
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


# Code
