# Intuition
- The problem asks us to find the maximum gap between any two elements in an array nums when the array is sorted. To do this, we can follow the following intuition:

- Sort the array nums in ascending order. Sorting is necessary because we want to find the maximum gap, and the maximum gap will likely occur between adjacent elements after sorting.

- Iterate through the sorted array and calculate the difference between each pair of adjacent elements. Keep track of the maximum difference found during this process.

- Return the maximum difference as the answer
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
1. Import the necessary library java.util for using Arrays.sort().

2. Define a function maximumGap that takes an array of integers nums as input and returns an integer representing the maximum gap.

3. Check if the length of nums is 1. If it is, return 0 because there is only one element, and there can be no gap.

4. Sort the nums array in ascending order using Arrays.sort(nums).

5. Initialize a variable max_diff to store the maximum gap and set it to 0.

6. Iterate through the sorted array from index 0 to nums.length - 2 (inclusive). For each pair of adjacent elements, calculate the difference curr_diff between them (i.e., nums[i+1] - nums[i]).

7. If curr_diff is greater than the current max_diff, update max_diff to be equal to curr_diff.

8. After the loop finishes, max_diff will contain the maximum gap between elements in the sorted array. Return max_diff as the result.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: `O(nlog(n))`
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: `O(1)`
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
import java.util.*;
class Solution {
    public int maximumGap(int[] nums) {
    Arrays.sort(nums);
    int max_diff = 0;
    if(nums.length == 1) {
        return 0;
    } 
    for(int i=0;i<nums.length-1;i++) {
        int curr_diff = nums[i+1]-nums[i];
        if(curr_diff > max_diff) {
            max_diff = curr_diff;
        }
    }
    return max_diff;
    }
}
```

