In this problem we are building up our table by the product of the previous element with 2,3 or 5 accordingly.(Minimum Product). We are using three different variables a,b,c to mark the the index of the previous elements which are a product of 2,3 or 5 respectively. 
The 3 different variables ensure that the table is generated effectively.[ For Eg : 1,2,3,4,5,6,8..... and not 1,2,3,5,10...  You see 4 which is the product of 2x2 .  The 3 variables make sure that their respective values are incremented  **IF and ONLY IF   the current element is a product of either 2 or 3 or 5 respectively **]
```
class Solution {
public:
    int nthUglyNumber(int n) {
        int ar[n];
        ar[0]=1;        
       int a=0,b=0,c=0,i=1;
        while(i<n)
        {
            ar[i]=min({ar[a]*2,ar[b]*3,ar[c]*5});
            if(ar[i]==ar[a]*2)
                a++;
         if(ar[i]==ar[b]*3)
                b++;
          if(ar[i]==ar[c]*5)
                c++;
            i++;
        }
        return ar[n-1];
    }
};
```

