Let us look at the ugly number sequence : 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 9, 10, 12, 15, …

Every number in the sequence is either divisible by 2 or 3 or 5.
So, we can look at the sequence as 3 groups of sequences
1) 1x2 , 2x2 , 3x2 , 4x2 , 5x2 , 6x2 , ...
2) 1x3 , 2x3 , 3x3 , 4x3 , 5x3 , 6x3 , ...
3) 1x5 , 2x5 , 3x5 , 4x5 , 5x5 , 6x5 , ...

Hence we use similar merge method as merge sort, to get every ugly number from the three subsequences. Every step, we choose the smallest one from the three sequences and move further.

**Approach :** DP
**Time and Space Complexities :** Time Complexity : O(n)
                                                            Auxiliary space : O(n)
**Algorithm :**
```
