QUES: find n th ugly.
##### **OBSERVATONS**
- maximum powers needed to do the job : 11 as 2^11 >1690 (thus 5^11 or 3^11 will be hell lot bigger)
- Thus only we need to permute power=i for numbers where i<=11
-  Now we have to find nth, it means nth smallest of all numbers formed
-  Thus we need to store values as we create ugly numbers in a sorted manner[set will be apt]
-  sorted manner helps us to create next smallest number too
-  One more thing, if top element of set is suppose 7. then next numbers will be 7\*2=14,7\*3=21, 7\*5=35:   Here we missed out a fact that 7\*4 is smaller than 7\*5 in the long run it might make difference so include that too;
Thus 7\*2=14, 7\*3=21, 7\*4=28, 7\*5=35

#### PSEUDO CODE
- create set with first element as 1
- c=1     ......................................................//COUNT SMALLEST UGLY NUMBERS
- while loop until c < n:
	- remove top
	- c++
	- check c==n   then ans=c 
	- add top\*2, top\*3, top\*4, top\*5 to set
	- REPEAT


Do 👍 upvote if found useful ❤️

