solutions.content:
The next ugly number is Min(existing ugly numbers * 2, existing ugly numbers * 3, existing ugly numbers * 5).  Each existing ugly number will be multiplied by 2, 3 and 5 once and only once, hence we use 3 pointers to track what would be the next **minimum** ulgy number.

```
public class Solution {
    public int NthUglyNumber(int n) {

        int[] arr = new int[n];
        arr[0] = 1;
        int p2 = 0, p3 = 0, p5 = 0;

        for(int i = 1; i < n; i++)
        {
            int num1 = 2 * arr[p2];
            int num2 = 3 * arr[p3];
            int num3 = 5 * arr[p5];

            arr[i] = Math.Min(num1, Math.Min(num2, num3));

            if(num1 == arr[i])
                p2++;
            if(num2 == arr[i])
                p3++;
            if(num3 == arr[i])
                p5++;
        }

        return arr[n-1];
    }
}
```

