    def canIWin(self, maxInt: int, total: int) -> bool:
        @functools.lru_cache(None)
        def dp(nums, left):
            return any(left - n <= 0 or not dp(frozenset(nums - {n}), left - n) for n in nums)

        return  (1 + maxInt) * maxInt // 2 >= total and dp(frozenset(range(1, maxInt + 1)), total)
```

```(1 + maxInt) * maxInt // 2 >= total``` - this makes sure that first player can even win (sum of the +1 series)
```frozenset(range(1, maxInt + 1)``` - creates hashable set possible numbers [1, 2, ..., maxInt]
Now, in each recursive call, we check for all nums if it's possible to win drawing one of them:
1. Either ```left - n <= 0``` which means that taking than number n will allow reaching the total or else..
2. ```not dp(frozenset(nums - {n}), left - n)``` - which means that your opponent cannot win using numbers which left.

```frozenset(nums - {n})``` - creates fresh new hashable set without n

We also cache by pair (nums, left) - every unique set of numbers is different.

